member.name: M:EVE.ISXEVE.DataTypes.ChatChannel.Send(System.String)
member.summary: 'Send' will broadcast any utf-8 string to the channel with the current player as the person speaking the text. 'Send' has a global throttle of one message ever 5 seconds, except for the "Local" channel in Jita; in that channel only one message every 40 seconds is allowed. (These throttles only apply to using the "Send" method of the channel datatype. You can still type messages and send them manually as often as you want.) The throttles begin when ISXEVE is loaded.

member.name: M:EVE.ISXEVE.DataTypes.ChatChannel.Echo(System.String)
member.summary: 'Echo' sends text to the local client's window, but NOT to other players in the channel. In other words, it's a "local echo only". The second argument is optional but will set who the message is "from" -- if no second argument is provided, it will be "from" the current player. (Sidebar: the charID# for "EVE System" is 1.)
